                          <p align="left">we live in an ever changing world<br>
                            common enough statement, but with a ring of the<br>
                            ominous<br>
                            rephrase that i will..<br>
                            we live in a world of ever changing values<br>
                            and priorities<br>
                            and opinions and ambitions<br>
                            and limits and excesses<br>
                            all changes, except the constancy of our temporal<br>
                            sojourn hereabouts<br>
                            what meaning it all has<br>
                            and to what purpose<br>
                            the quest for the truth of these<br>
                            probably defines for most a reason<br>
                            to exist and continue to exist<br>
                            to love and cherish and jealously guard<br>
                            the ability to breath in and exhale<br>
                            fascinating to me it is<br>
                            it remains the one thing that still captivates<br>
                            this quest to know<br>
                            what meaning is there is to man<br>
